tton you wish to add.</p>\n<p>If you are not using the  Quicktags i.e. using the WYSIWYG or you want to do it manually, you can add <code>&lt;!--reddit_1--&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;!--reddit_2--&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;!--reddit_3--&gt;</code> where you want to display the button. For correct XHTML, make sure that the code is added on a new line. </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://ajaydsouza.com/wordpress/plugins/reddit-button/\">Read more and download the reddit button plugin &gt;&gt;</a></p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Wed, 06 Sep 2006 19:01:08 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:4:\"Ajay\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:886:\"<p>I have just released <a href=\"http://ajaydsouza.com/wordpress/plugins/reddit-button/\">The reddit button Plugin</a> for WordPress.</p>\n<p>You can use this plugin to insert a <a href=\"http://reddit.com/buttons\">reddit button</a> for your post.</p>\n<p>This plugin automatically adds a button to the QuickTags toolbar in the post screen. Clicking the button will prompt you to insert the style of the button you wish to add.</p>\n<p>If you are not using the  Quicktags i.e. using the WYSIWYG or you want to do it manually, you can add <code>&lt;!--reddit_1--&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;!--reddit_2--&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;!--reddit_3--&gt;</code> where you want to display the button. For correct XHTML, make sure that the code is added on a new line. </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://ajaydsouza.com/wordpress/plugins/reddit-button/\">Read more and download the reddit button plugin &gt;&gt;</a></p>\";}i:13;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:43:\"Weblog Tools Collection: WP Theme: Dalarnas\";s:4:\"guid\";s:71:\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2006/09/06/wp-theme-dalarnas/\";s:4:\"link\";s:70:\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/19813427/\";s:11:\"description\";s:184:\"<p><a href=\"http://proletarium.org/proyectos/dalarnas/\">WP Theme: Dalarnas</a> Two column crisp theme for Wordpress that reminds me of the original Digg site. Lots of white space.\n</p>\"