collection.com/archives/2006/08/29/sixapart-vox/\";s:4:\"link\";s:70:\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/17479016/\";s:11:\"description\";s:802:\"<p><a href=\"http://www.sixapart.com/vox/\">SixApart Vox</a> So where is <a href=\"http://www.sixapart.com/vox/index\">VOX</a>? I remember a bunch of <a href=\"http://www.techcrunch.com/2006/05/31/sixapart-to-launch-comet-renamed-vox-on-june-1/\">hoopla</a> on the original Comet hosted blogging platform and remember thinking to myself that they are following the same path as Wordpress.com with a small and private group of users with plans expanded to a larger audience while they learn the ropes of their new software. Most of <a href=\"http://www.vox.com/explore/posts/\">the stuff</a> looks like a web 2.0 rehash of most things cool put together with LiveJournal. Anyone use VOX? PS: I wonder if FeedBurner had to fix their &#8220;xx readers&#8221; script to accomodate TechCrunch&#8217;s cool 100k.\n</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Tue, 29 Aug 2006 23:32:19 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:4:\"Mark\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:802:\"<p><a href=\"http://www.sixapart.com/vox/\">SixApart Vox</a> So where is <a href=\"http://www.sixapart.com/vox/index\">VOX</a>? I remember a bunch of <a href=\"http://www.techcrunch.com/2006/05/31/sixapart-to-launch-comet-renamed-vox-on-june-1/\">hoopla</a> on the original Comet hosted blogging platform and remember thinking to myself that they are following the same path as Wordpress.com with a small and private group of users with plans expanded to a larger audience while they learn the ropes of their new software. Most of <a href=\"http://www.vox.com/explore/posts/\">the stuff</a> looks like a web 2.0 rehash of most things cool put together with LiveJournal. Anyone use VOX? PS: I wonder if FeedBurner had to fix their &#8220;xx readers&#8221; script to accomodate TechCrunch&#8217;s cool 100k.\n</p>\";}i:33;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:25:\"Matt: Scooped by a Source\";s:4:\"guid\";s:52:\"http://photomatt.net/2006/08/29/scooped-by-a-source/\";s:4:\"link\";s:52:\"http://photomatt.net/2006/08/29/scooped-by-a-source/\";s:11:\"description\";s:430:\"<p><a href=\"http://mediabistro.com/articles/cache/a8356.asp\">Scooped by a Source</a>. \"\'I think you\'re assuming that there is any value left in the scoop,\' wrote <a href=\"http://buzzmachine.com/\">Jeff Jarvis</a>, blogger and citizen journalism advocate, in an email. \'There isn\'t. You can\'t control the biorhythms of news anymore. The world doesn\'t much care who reported what first. Bylines matter to writers, not readers.\'\"\n</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Tue, 29 Aug 2006 20:27:26 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:4:\"Matt\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:430:\"<p><a href=\"http://mediabistro.com/articles/cache/a8356.asp\">Scooped by a Source</a>. \"\'I think you\'re assuming that there is any value left in the scoop,\' wrote <a href=\"http://buzzmachine.com/\">Jeff Jarvis</a>, blogger and citizen journalism advocate, in an email. \'There isn\'t. You can\'t control the biorhythms of news anymore. The world doesn\'t much care who reported what first. Bylines matter to writers, not readers.\'\"\n</p>\";}i:34;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:46:\"Weblog Tools Collection: WP Plugin: WP-Galeria\";s:4:\"guid\";s:74:\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2006/08/29/wp-plugin-wp-galeria/\";s:4:\"link\";s:70:\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/17425501/\";s:11:\"description\";s:338:\"<p><a href=\"http://spy98.bitshifters.net/wordpress-plugins/wp-galeria/\">WP Plugin: WP-Galeria</a> Is a simple files and folder based gallery plugin for Wordpress that supports zip file upload, on the fly thumbnail creation and comes with a couple of premade templates derived from Kubrick and k2. I did not notice an example gallery.\n</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Tue, 29 Aug 2006 19:45:28 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:4:\"Mark\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:338:\"<p><a href=\"http://spy98.bitshifters.n