st on their forums</a>, I was able to get I installed. Thanks Roger from 456 Berea Street.\n</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Tue, 29 Aug 2006 09:10:06 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:4:\"Mark\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:400:\"<p><a href=\"http://www.getswift.org/alpha.html\">Swift: Safari for Windows</a> Still in alpha, but based on the Apple Webkit rendering engine and already a downloadable product. I could not get it to install on my XP laptop. EDIT: After reading <a href=\"http://bbs.getwebkit.org/viewtopic.php?t=48\">this post on their forums</a>, I was able to get I installed. Thanks Roger from 456 Berea Street.\n</p>\";}i:37;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:62:\"Weblog Tools Collection: Readability and High Contrast Designs\";s:4:\"guid\";s:91:\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2006/08/29/readability-and-high-contrast-designs/\";s:4:\"link\";s:70:\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/17263248/\";s:11:\"description\";s:453:\"<p><a href=\"http://www.456bereastreet.com/archive/200608/light_text_on_dark_background_vs_readability/\">Readability and High Contrast Designs</a> Roger takes on the light text on dark background folks and opns up a can of worms. However, the reasoning is sounds and though the dislike and readability impairment might be limited, the bookmarklet and valuable discussion is worth the read. Do you like dark on light designs as much as light on dark?\n</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Tue, 29 Aug 2006 09:01:14 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:4:\"Mark\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:453:\"<p><a href=\"http://www.456bereastreet.com/archive/200608/light_text_on_dark_background_vs_readability/\">Readability and High Contrast Designs</a> Roger takes on the light text on dark background folks and opns up a can of worms. However, the reasoning is sounds and though the dislike and readability impairment might be limited, the bookmarklet and valuable discussion is worth the read. Do you like dark on light designs as much as light on dark?\n</p>\";}i:38;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:23:\"Matt: Web Scaling Books\";s:4:\"guid\";s:50:\"http://photomatt.net/2006/08/28/web-scaling-books/\";s:4:\"link\";s:50:\"http://photomatt.net/2006/08/28/web-scaling-books/\";s:11:\"description\";s:812:\"<p>I\'ve read two really good books on scaling large-scale web applications lately: <cite><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0596102356/sr=8-3/qid=1156827416/ref=pd_bbs_3/102-2469871-3619369?ie=UTF8\">Building Scalable Websites</a></cite> by Cal Henderson and <cite><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/067232699X/sr=8-1/qid=1156827416/ref=pd_bbs_1/102-2469871-3619369?ie=UTF8\">Scalable Internet Architectures</a></cite> by Theo Schlossnagle. (Original titles, eh?) Both dispel common myths and misconceptions about scaling. While neither maps directly to the approaches we\'re taking at Automattic, they\'re both must-read for developers approaching or past the million/day pageview mark. I only wish I had more time to discuss my thoughts on the various concepts in the books---particularly Cal\'s.\n</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Tue, 29 Aug 2006 05:03:50 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:4:\"Matt\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:812:\"<p>I\'ve read two really good books on scaling large-scale web applications lately: <cite><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0596102356/sr=8-3/qid=1156827416/ref=pd_bbs_3/102-2469871-3619369?ie=UTF8\">Building Scalable Websites</a></cite> by Cal Henderson and <cite><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/067232699X/sr=8-1/qid=1156827416/ref=pd_bbs_1/102-2469871-3619369?ie=UTF8\">Scalable Internet Architectures</a></cite> by Theo Schlossnagle. (Original titles, eh?) Both dispel common myths and misconceptions about scaling. While neither maps directly to the approaches we\'re taking at Automattic, they\'re both must-read for developers approaching or past the million/day pageview mark. I only wish I had more time to discuss my thoughts on the various concepts in the books---particularly Cal\'s.\n</p>\";}i:39;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:17:\"Akismet: Downtime\";s:4:\"guid\";s:41:\"http://akismet.com/blog/2006/08/downtime/\";s:4:\"link\";s:41:\"http://akismet.com/blog/2006/08/downtime/\";s:11:\"description\";s:1142:\"<p>The stats code introduced yesterday had a bug which only triggered about 24 hours after it had launched. It kicked in for different blogs at different times, but the result was that starting sometime last night you probably started to see really obvious spam getting past your Akismet filters.</p>\n<p>All of our systems were up and running at the time, and spam was being correctly identified, which is why our monitoring systems didn&#8217;t notify us of the problem. However, there was extra junk being included with the response which broke the API call, which expects only &#8220;true&#8221; or &#8220;false&#8221;.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m really sorry about this, when things are working smoothly it&#8217;s easy to forget how much vile junk is actually being blocked day to day. I&#8217;m going to go through my blogs now and double-check that no spam actually got published, and I&#8217;d suggest other folks do the same. The &#8220;mass edit&#8221; mode under &#8220;Comments&#8221; should be useful for WordPress users.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;ve also taken steps to make sure on the Akismet side this kind of error can&#8217;t happen again.\n</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Sun, 27 Aug 2006 18:00:48 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:14:\"Matt Mullenweg\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:1142:\"<p>The stats code introduced yesterday had a bug which only triggered about 24 hours after it had launched. It kicked in for different blogs at different times, but the result was that starting sometime last night you probably started to see really obvious spam getting past your Akismet filters.</p>\n<p>All of our systems were up and running at the time, and spam was being correctly identified, which is why our monitoring systems didn&#8217;t notify us of the problem. However, there was extra junk being included with the response which broke the API call, which expects only &#8220;true&#8221; or &#8220;false&#8221;.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m really sorry about this, when things are working smoothly it&#8217;s easy to forget how much vile junk is actually being blocked day to day. I&#8217;m going to go through my blogs now and double-check that no spam actually got published, and I&#8217;d suggest other folks do the same. The &#8220;mass edit&#8221; mode under &#8220;Comments&#8221; should be useful for WordPress users.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;ve also taken steps to make sure on the Akismet side this kind of error can&#8217;t happen again.\n</p>\";}i:40;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:40:\"Weblog Tools Collection: WP Theme: Ebony\";s:4:\"guid\";s:68:\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2006/08/27/wp-theme-ebony/\";s:4:\"link\";s:70:\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/16771884/\";s:11:\"description\";s:217:\"<p><a href=\"http://webgazette.co.uk/wordpress-themes/ebony/\">WP Theme: Ebony</a> Ebony is a 2 column, light on dark, fixed width theme and features a widget enabled sidebar and is fully prepared for localisation.\n</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Sun, 27 Aug 2006 15:29:04 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:4:\"Mark\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:217:\"<p><a href=\"http://webgazette.co.uk/wordpress-themes/ebony/\">WP Theme: Ebony</a> Ebony is a 2 column, light on dark, fixed width theme and features a widget enabled sidebar and is fully prepared for localisation.\n</p>\";}i:41;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:47:\"Weblog Tools Collection: WP Theme: Bright Pixel\";s:4:\"guid\";s:75:\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2006/08/27/wp-theme-bright-pixel/\";s:4:\"link\";s:70:\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/16757565/\";s:11:\"description\";s:199:\"<p><a href=\"http://www.kaushalsheth.com/bright-pixel-wordpress-theme-released/\">WP Theme: Bright Pixel</a>  is a single column smooth, monochrome, lightweight wordpress theme in shades of white.\n</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Sun, 27 Aug 2006 14:14:59 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:7:\"Kaushal\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:199:\"<p><a href=\"http://www.kaushalsheth.com/bright-pixel-wordpress-theme-released/\">WP Theme: Bright Pixel</a>  is a single column smooth, monochrome, lightweight wordpress theme in shades of white.\n</p>\";}i:42;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:21:\"Akismet: Better Stats\";s:4:\"guid\";s:45:\"http://akismet.com/blog/2006/08/better-stats/\";s:4:\"link\";s:45:\"http://akismet.com/blog/2006/08/better-stats/\";s:11:\"description\";s:570:\"<p>We did some upgrades to the system last night to do some more finely grained tracking of the per blog and per key amounts of spam, ham, and mistakes moving through the system. It&#8217;s starting to expose some interesting data, and it&#8217;s kinda fun to play with. I&#8217;m curious if folks would be interested in getting access to the data for their key, daily stats and such? No graphs yet, but that&#8217;s a logical next step.</p>\n<p><b>Update:</b> This upgrade had a bug <a href=\"http://akismet.com/blog/2006/08/downtime/\">that caused some downtime</a>.\n</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Sun, 27 Aug 2006 01:59:51 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:14:\"Matt Mullenweg\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:570:\"<p>We did some upgrades to the system last night to do some more finely grained tracking of the per blog and per key amounts of spam, ham, and mistakes moving through the system. It&#8217;s starting to expose some interesting data, and it&#8217;s kinda fun to play with. I&#8217;m curious if folks would be interested in getting access to the data for their key, daily stats and such? No graphs yet, but that&#8217;s a logical next step.</p>\n<p><b>Update:</b> This upgrade had a bug <a href=\"http://akismet.com/blog/2006/08/downtime/\">that caused some downtime</a>.\n</p>\";}i:43;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:39:\"Matt: 5 Reasons to Use WordPress as CMS\";s:4:\"guid\";s:46:\"http://photomatt.net/20